DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(93)90079-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387893900793
AB  - This paper shows that if because of administration costs or other wastes only a proportion of an aid reaches the recipient, then it is possible that the donor is enriched by its act of charity, the extent of the enrichment increasing with the extent of the leakage, and/or that the recipient is impoverished by aid, the extent of the impoverishment increasing with the extent of the leakage. These outcomes are possible even when trade is optimally restricted by donor or recipient.
ER  - 
